.TH "blkdev_get_by_path" 9 "blkdev_get_by_path" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
blkdev_get_by_path \- open a block device by name
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "struct block_device *" blkdev_get_by_path
.BI "(const char *path "  ","
.BI "fmode_t mode "  ","
.BI "void *holder "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "path" 12
path to the block device to open
.IP "mode" 12
FMODE_* mask
.IP "holder" 12
exclusive holder identifier
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Open the block device described by the device file at \fIpath\fP.  If \fImode\fP
includes FMODE_EXCL, the block device is opened with exclusive access.
Specifying FMODE_EXCL with a NULL \fIholder\fP is invalid.  Exclusive opens may
nest for the same \fIholder\fP.
.SH "CONTEXT"
Might sleep.
.SH "RETURN"
Reference to the block_device on success, ERR_PTR(-errno) on failure.
